
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                 SKonf : Shinken Monitoring Configuration Tool              |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+

What is SKonf ?
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+

	SKonf is a configuration tool dedicated to ease the configuration of
	Shinken distributed and high availibility architecures. 
	
What is NOT SKonf ?
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+

	SKonf is not another monitoring console (and will never be). 
	There are numerous monitoring console available and ready to use with
	Shinken (Ex: Thruk, Ninga, Nagios CGI ....).
	
	SKonf is not another configuration tool dedicated to add/remove hosts
	services ... etc ... (but it should/will be !)

Installation
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------+

	SKonf is now bundled with Shinken. There are a few steps to do manualy
	in order to activate SKonf. Running skonf through apache is not ready yet
	Edit shinken/skon/settings.py and modify SHINKEN_PATH to match your 
	installation. Then run 'python manage.py runserver' to start the
	config tool. You can now access it in your browser at the following
	URL :  http://localhost:8000

